Authors@R: person("Joe", "Watson", email = "joe.watson@stat.ubc.ca",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package performs a Monte Carlo test for preferential    
    sampling in spatio-temporal data. This includes geostatistical, 
    discrete spatial and time series data types. For the geostatistical
    setting, a spatial point process must be specified using the spatstat
    package. For the discrete spatial setting, a binary regression model 
    must be specified over the fixed collection of areal units. For the 
    time series data, a one-dimensional point process model must be
    specified using the spatstat package.
